Usage: findPinPortNumber [-help] [-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}] [-bumps <string>]
                         [-geometry_height {min [max]}]
                         [-geometry_width {min [max]}] [-layer <string>] {[-cellName <string> | -instName <string>] [-selected ]} {-pinName <string> | -netName <string>}

-help                           # Prints out the command usage
-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}             # specifies in which area that the command will
                                # be used (box, optional)
-bumps <string>                 # find pin port num for bumps
                                # (string, optional)
-cellName <string>              # find pin port num of instance of specified
                                # cell (string, required)
-geometry_height {min [max]}    # Specifies the range of the height of the
                                # geometry of the target port and if only one
                                # variable, the height is equal with the
                                # specified value (string, optional)
-geometry_width {min [max]}     # Specifies the range of the width of the
                                # geometry of the target port and if only one
                                # variable, the width is equal with the
                                # specified value (string, optional)
-instName <string>              # find pin port num of specified instance
                                # (string, required)
-layer <string>                 # Specifies the name of the layer on which the
                                # target port is (string, optional)
-netName <string>               # find port num on pin connectted to specified
                                # net (string, required)
-pinName <string>               # find port num on specified pin
                                # (string, required)
-selected                       # find pin port num of selected instance
                                # (bool, required)